AJ Swearingen has been performing this music for twenty years with mastery of Paul Simon's intricate guitar playing. His deep baritone blends perfectly against Kelli's angelic vocals, which invoke a true sound in the spirit of Art Garfunkel. Two voices, in perfect harmony, balanced against one acoustic guitar delivers a true tribute to the sound of the 1960's Greenwich Village, NY coffeehouse performances. Aj, born in Bethlehem PA, and Jayne, from Lapeer MI, met in 2009 at a singer-songwriters club in St. Petersburg, FL. Magnetically drawn to each other's songwriting and performing, they quickly discovered a signature vocal blend. They produced and released their debut album together in 2013. Folk icon Tom Rush recorded and included their song "You're not here with me" on his album What I Know. The pair continues to write, record and tour nationally with their repertoire of alt-country and folk style in addition to their beloved recreation of Simon & Garfunkel's music. Together and separately, Swearingen & Kelli have shared the stage with artists including Kenny Rogers, Crystal Gayle, Livingston Taylor, Dave Mason and more.
